{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016J3asDUXVSyt74LxRybyW3","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: kube-agent\n     3→description: |\n     4→  Run kube-agent.sh — a lean Kubernetes manifest validator that produces agent-friendly output.\n     5→  Use when: running Kubernetes manifest validation, kubeconform checks, kubeval checks, verifying K8s manifests before applying,\n     6→  or when the user asks to validate Kubernetes YAML, run k8s checks, or check manifests.\n     7→  Triggers on: kube agent, kubernetes validate, kubeconform, kubeval, k8s checks, validate manifests.\n     8→context: fork\n     9→allowed-tools:\n    10→  - Bash(scripts/kube-agent.sh*)\n    11→  - Bash(RUN_*=* scripts/kube-agent.sh*)\n    12→  - Bash(KUBE_SCHEMAS_DIR=* scripts/kube-agent.sh*)\n    13→  - Bash(MAX_LINES=* scripts/kube-agent.sh*)\n    14→  - Bash(KEEP_DIR=* scripts/kube-agent.sh*)\n    15→  - Bash(FAIL_FAST=* scripts/kube-agent.sh*)\n    16→  - Bash(CHANGED_FILES=* scripts/kube-agent.sh*)\n    17→  - Bash(TMPDIR_ROOT=* scripts/kube-agent.sh*)\n    18→---\n    19→\n    20→# Kube Agent\n    21→\n    22→Run the `kube-agent.sh` script for lean, structured Kubernetes manifest validation output designed for coding agents.\n    23→\n    24→## Script Location\n    25→\n    26→```\n    27→scripts/kube-agent.sh\n    28→```\n    29→\n    30→## Usage\n    31→\n    32→### Run Full Suite (validate)\n    33→```bash\n    34→scripts/kube-agent.sh\n    35→```\n    36→\n    37→### Run Individual Steps\n    38→```bash\n    39→scripts/kube-agent.sh validate  # validate manifests only\n    40→scripts/kube-agent.sh all       # full suite (default)\n    41→```\n    42→\n    43→## Environment Knobs\n    44→\n    45→| Variable | Default | Description |\n    46→|----------|---------|-------------|\n    47→| `RUN_VALIDATE` | `1` | Set to `0` to skip validate step |\n    48→| `KUBE_SCHEMAS_DIR` | _(empty)_ | Custom schema location for validator |\n    49→| `FAIL_FAST` | `0` | Set to `1` to stop after first failure (or use `--fail-fast`) |\n    50→| `CHANGED_FILES` | _(empty)_ | Space-separated changed file paths; scopes to matching manifests |\n    51→| `MAX_LINES` | `40` | Max output lines printed per step (unlimited in CI) |\n    52→| `KEEP_DIR` | `0` | Set to `1` to keep temp log dir on success |\n    53→\n    54→## Output Format\n    55→\n    56→- Each step prints a header (`Step: validate`)\n    57→- Results are `PASS`, `FAIL`, or `SKIP`\n    58→- On failure, output is truncated to `MAX_LINES`\n    59→- Full logs are saved to a temp directory (path printed in output)\n    60→- Overall result is printed at the end: `Overall: PASS` or `Overall: FAIL`\n    61→\n    62→## Important Notes\n    63→\n    64→- Prefers `kubeconform` over `kubeval`; exits with code 2 if neither is installed\n    65→- Discovers `.yml`/`.yaml` files containing both `apiVersion:` and `kind:`\n    66→- Excludes `.git/`, `.github/`, `node_modules/`, and `charts/` directories\n    67→- `CHANGED_FILES` scopes validation to only the specified files\n    68→- Reports SKIP when no Kubernetes manifests are found\n    69→- In CI (`CI=true`), `MAX_LINES` defaults to unlimited; locally it defaults to 40\n    70→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"85fc0a59-c739-40c4-adb1-d8ca4c9716cd","uuid":"4b1c28f8-d646-42f5-8aea-7824164538e6","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/skills/kube-agent/SKILL.md","content":"---\nname: kube-agent\ndescription: |\n  Run kube-agent.sh — a lean Kubernetes manifest validator that produces agent-friendly output.\n  Use when: running Kubernetes manifest validation, kubeconform checks, kubeval checks, verifying K8s manifests before applying,\n  or when the user asks to validate Kubernetes YAML, run k8s checks, or check manifests.\n  Triggers on: kube agent, kubernetes validate, kubeconform, kubeval, k8s checks, validate manifests.\ncontext: fork\nallowed-tools:\n  - Bash(scripts/kube-agent.sh*)\n  - Bash(RUN_*=* scripts/kube-agent.sh*)\n  - Bash(KUBE_SCHEMAS_DIR=* scripts/kube-agent.sh*)\n  - Bash(MAX_LINES=* scripts/kube-agent.sh*)\n  - Bash(KEEP_DIR=* scripts/kube-agent.sh*)\n  - Bash(FAIL_FAST=* scripts/kube-agent.sh*)\n  - Bash(CHANGED_FILES=* scripts/kube-agent.sh*)\n  - Bash(TMPDIR_ROOT=* scripts/kube-agent.sh*)\n---\n\n# Kube Agent\n\nRun the `kube-agent.sh` script for lean, structured Kubernetes manifest validation output designed for coding agents.\n\n## Script Location\n\n```\nscripts/kube-agent.sh\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n### Run Full Suite (validate)\n```bash\nscripts/kube-agent.sh\n```\n\n### Run Individual Steps\n```bash\nscripts/kube-agent.sh validate  # validate manifests only\nscripts/kube-agent.sh all       # full suite (default)\n```\n\n## Environment Knobs\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `RUN_VALIDATE` | `1` | Set to `0` to skip validate step |\n| `KUBE_SCHEMAS_DIR` | _(empty)_ | Custom schema location for validator |\n| `FAIL_FAST` | `0` | Set to `1` to stop after first failure (or use `--fail-fast`) |\n| `CHANGED_FILES` | _(empty)_ | Space-separated changed file paths; scopes to matching manifests |\n| `MAX_LINES` | `40` | Max output lines printed per step (unlimited in CI) |\n| `KEEP_DIR` | `0` | Set to `1` to keep temp log dir on success |\n\n## Output Format\n\n- Each step prints a header (`Step: validate`)\n- Results are `PASS`, `FAIL`, or `SKIP`\n- On failure, output is truncated to `MAX_LINES`\n- Full logs are saved to a temp directory (path printed in output)\n- Overall result is printed at the end: `Overall: PASS` or `Overall: FAIL`\n\n## Important Notes\n\n- Prefers `kubeconform` over `kubeval`; exits with code 2 if neither is installed\n- Discovers `.yml`/`.yaml` files containing both `apiVersion:` and `kind:`\n- Excludes `.git/`, `.github/`, `node_modules/`, and `charts/` directories\n- `CHANGED_FILES` scopes validation to only the specified files\n- Reports SKIP when no Kubernetes manifests are found\n- In CI (`CI=true`), `MAX_LINES` defaults to unlimited; locally it defaults to 40\n","numLines":70,"startLine":1,"totalLines":70}}}
