{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0176YqU9APc4hGFCYFA2Mqhx","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/.ralph/exploration.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"85fc0a59-c739-40c4-adb1-d8ca4c9716cd","uuid":"79afdbaf-f4ad-4182-9a80-71f0f3f4d96a","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/.ralph/exploration.md","oldString":"- `CHANGED_FILES` is optional and used only where meaningful; if non-empty, logic narrows execution targets.","newString":"- `CHANGED_FILES` is optional and used only where meaningful; if non-empty, logic narrows execution targets.\n- `KUBE_IGNORE_MISSING_SCHEMAS=1` enables offline-safe validation by skipping resources whose schemas can't be fetched; all kube-agent test fixtures use this knob for network independence.","originalFile":"# x-agent Exploration Notes\n\n## Key Files & Roles\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/AGENTS.md`: global agent conventions and output contract.\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/lib/x-agent-common.sh`: shared Bash helpers used by all agents (`step`, `print_result`, `fmt_elapsed`, `setup_outdir`, `should_continue`, lock helpers, `need`).\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/run-scenarios.sh`: discovery/execution harness for `clean`, `issues`, and additional fixture directories.\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/skills/gha-agent/scripts/gha-agent.sh`: reference for scoped filtering and simple discovery helper patterns.\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/skills/helm-agent/scripts/helm-agent.sh`: reference for multi-command agents and chart/scoping patterns.\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/skills/bash-agent/scripts/bash-agent.sh`: reference for universal output and fail-fast wiring.\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/skills/terra-agent/scripts/terra-agent.sh`: reference for alternate validation modes and dependency behavior.\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/docs/agents/add-x-agent.md`: onboarding pattern for SKILL.md and allowed-tools.\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/docs/agents/scenario-tests.md`: scenario fixture contract and required fields.\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/skills/kube-agent/scripts/kube-agent.sh`: Kubernetes manifest validator (kubeconform/kubeval) — discovers `.yml`/`.yaml` with `apiVersion:`+`kind:`, excludes `.git/`, `.github/`, `node_modules/`, `charts/`.\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/skills/kube-agent/SKILL.md`: agent metadata with triggers and allowed-tools.\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/kube-agent/clean/`: valid Deployment manifest fixture (EXPECT_EXIT=0).\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/kube-agent/issues/`: invalid Deployment manifest fixture (EXPECT_EXIT=1).\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/kube-agent/no-manifests/`: empty dir fixture for skip behavior (EXPECT_EXIT=0).\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/kube-agent/scoped-match/`: CHANGED_FILES scoping with matching manifest (EXPECT_EXIT=0).\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/kube-agent/scoped-no-match/`: CHANGED_FILES scoping with no matches, expects SKIP (EXPECT_EXIT=0).\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/kube-agent/non-k8s-yaml/`: non-Kubernetes YAML files only, verifies filter skips them (EXPECT_EXIT=0).\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/kube-agent/kubeval-clean/`: valid manifest with kubeval fallback via PATH wrapper (EXPECT_EXIT=0, REQUIRED_TOOLS=kubeval).\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/kube-agent/kubeval-issues/`: invalid manifest with kubeval fallback via PATH wrapper (EXPECT_EXIT=1, REQUIRED_TOOLS=kubeval).\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/kube-agent/schema-dir/`: KUBE_SCHEMAS_DIR passthrough smoke test (EXPECT_EXIT=0, REQUIRED_TOOLS=kubeconform).\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/kube-agent/run-with-kubeval.sh`: wrapper that hides kubeconform from PATH using shadow directories (preserves co-located kubeval) for kubeval fallback testing.\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/install.sh`: skill registry, dependency checks, and AGENTS/CLAUDE snippet generation.\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/README.md`: published agent inventory and usage examples.\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/.ralph/specs/07-kube-agent.md`: specification and explicit FR mapping.\n\n## Patterns & Conventions\n- Scripts use Bash 3.2-compatible syntax and start with `set -euo pipefail`.\n- `--help` / `help` / `-h` is handled before any tool checks so help works in environments without validators.\n- Required dependencies fail with exit code `2` using `need` or custom logic that prints explicit install guidance.\n- Output contract remains strict: each step prints `Step`, `Result`, optional `Fix` for failures, `Time`, and final `Overall` and `Logs`.\n- `CHANGED_FILES` is optional and used only where meaningful; if non-empty, logic narrows execution targets.\n- Scenario contract (`SCENARIO_NAME`, `AGENT_SCRIPT`, `RUN_ARGS`, `EXPECT_EXIT`, optional `REQUIRED_TOOLS`) is standardized in `tests/run-scenarios.sh`.\n- `shellcheck --severity=warning` runs across `skills/*`, `lib/*`, and test shell scripts before scenario execution.\n\n## Database Schema\n- No runtime DB/schema is used by the agent runtime or test harness.\n- State for loop execution lives in `.ralph` files (`ralph-state.json`, logs, and task iteration files).\n\n## Test Infrastructure\n- Core harness: `tests/run-scenarios.sh` discovers `tests/*/scenario.env`.\n- A fixture can set any env values consumed by the agent script, including `CHANGED_FILES` and `KUBE_SCHEMAS_DIR`.\n- Exit semantics: `EXPECT_EXIT=0` for pass, `1` for fail, `2` for config/dependency failure paths.\n- Tool availability is injected via `REQUIRED_TOOLS` in each `scenario.env`.\n- Existing test pattern: each new agent ships at least `clean/` and `issues/`, plus optional scoped/skip fixtures when FRs demand.\n- Scenario env vars that the agent script reads (e.g. `CHANGED_FILES`) must be `export`ed in `scenario.env` since the harness runs agent scripts as subprocesses.\n\n## Architecture & Data Flow\n- Input environment and CLI command enter the agent script.\n- Script resolves validator and candidate files, optionally filtered by `CHANGED_FILES`.\n- Validation runs once per step with logs written to `OUTDIR`.\n- Structured contract prints per-step and overall result, including actionable `Fix` lines.\n- Errors and skips are returned via exit codes while preserving logs for debugging.\n\n- Installer path: `install.sh` pulls from `SKILLS` list; for `kube-agent`, this list and optional checks must be extended.\n- Documentation path: `README.md` must stay aligned to skill script names and command set (`validate`, `all`, help variants).\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":32,"oldLines":6,"newStart":32,"newLines":7,"lines":[" - Required dependencies fail with exit code `2` using `need` or custom logic that prints explicit install guidance."," - Output contract remains strict: each step prints `Step`, `Result`, optional `Fix` for failures, `Time`, and final `Overall` and `Logs`."," - `CHANGED_FILES` is optional and used only where meaningful; if non-empty, logic narrows execution targets.","+- `KUBE_IGNORE_MISSING_SCHEMAS=1` enables offline-safe validation by skipping resources whose schemas can't be fetched; all kube-agent test fixtures use this knob for network independence."," - Scenario contract (`SCENARIO_NAME`, `AGENT_SCRIPT`, `RUN_ARGS`, `EXPECT_EXIT`, optional `REQUIRED_TOOLS`) is standardized in `tests/run-scenarios.sh`."," - `shellcheck --severity=warning` runs across `skills/*`, `lib/*`, and test shell scripts before scenario execution."," "]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
